# Required — your Floe API key.
#
# Two key formats are accepted:
#
#   floe_<64-hex>        — Agent key. Identifies one specific agent. Required
#                          for agent-awareness tools (credit-remaining, spend-limit,
#                          loan-state, etc). Recommended for most MCP setups.
#                          Mint one per agent in the dashboard or via
#                          `floe-agent register --name <name>` (agentkit-actions).
#
#   floe_live_<base62>   — Developer key. Scoped to the developer, not a single
#                          agent. Use only if you need to manage multiple agents
#                          from one MCP session; agent-awareness tools will 401.
#
# Mint agent keys via the agent setup wizard at https://dev-dashboard.floelabs.xyz
# (or `floe-agent register --name <name>`). Mint developer keys via the
# "API Keys" page at https://dev-dashboard.floelabs.xyz/keys.
FLOE_API_KEY=

# Optional — defaults to https://credit-api.floelabs.xyz
# FLOE_API_BASE_URL=

# Optional — HTTP server port (non-stdio mode only)
# MCP_PORT=3100

# Optional — bind address for HTTP mode (default: 127.0.0.1)
# MCP_HOST=0.0.0.0

# Optional — allow unauthenticated requests to use the server's FLOE_API_KEY (default: false)
# ALLOW_SHARED_KEY_FALLBACK=true
